    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Java 8 now supports BASE64 Encoding and Decoding. You can use the following classes:\n<code>java.util.Base64</code>, <code>java.util.Base64.Encoder</code> and <code>java.util.Base64.Decoder</code>.</p>\n\n<p>Example usage:</p>\n\n<pre><code>// encode with padding\nString encoded = Base64.getEncoder().encodeToString(someByteArray);\n\n// encode without padding\nString encoded = Base64.getEncoder().withoutPadding().encodeToString(someByteArray);\n\n// decode a String\nbyte [] barr = Base64.getDecoder().decode(encoded); \n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
